    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8783" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τελαμών</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῶνος</span> (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ταλ</span>): any belt
          or strap to <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bear</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">support</span> something,
          hence (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">sword-belt, baldric</span> (see cuts Nos. 86,
          109).—(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shield-strap</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            11.610</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.404</span></i> (see
          cut).—(3) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">thong</span> attached to the ankles of a dead body,
          to drag it away, <i><span class="en">Il. 17.290</span></i>. (Cf. cut
          No. 16.) 
